Another skill being lost to archives is cruising around on low angle ice. It’s an interesting phenomenon as I often see climbers flying up WI 5 and even WI 6 but struggling to move around on the ground on low angle ice😬
.
These are the skills that can really help in the mountains on alpine routes. No big deal if you just crag at Ouray and only want to climb steep ice but if some of your goals are alpine routes that can get scrappy then spend some time learning how to flat foot!

Mount Dukono, located on Halmahera Island in Indonesia’s Maluku Province, is one of the most active volcanoes in the region. As a stratovolcano, it has frequent eruptions, emitting powerful ash plumes and lava flows that captivate both researchers and adventurers. The volcano’s geological features make it a prime subject for volcanology studies. Its eruptions are often unpredictable, making it an exciting yet dangerous destination for those seeking a volcano adventure. Situated in a remote destination, Dukono is a spectacular sight, representing the raw power of nature. It remains one of the most notable active volcanoes in Indonesia.

🟥 OUTLINE ITINERARY :

✅Day 4 :Rest & acclimatization at Namche
✅Day 5 :Trek from Namche (3,440m) to Tengboche/ Deboche (3,855m )
✅Day 6 :Trek from Tengboche (3,855m ) to Dingboche (4,360m )
✅Day 7: Rest & acclimatization at Dingboche
✅Day 8: Trek from Dingboche (4,360m ) to Lobuche (4,930m )
✅Day 9: Trek from Lobuche (4,930m ) to EBC (5,364m ) and back to Gorak Shep (5,185m )
✅Day 10: Hike to Kala Patthar(5,555m ) viewpoint, trek to Gorak Shep then to Pheriche (4,250m)
✅Day 11: Trek from Pheriche (4,250m ) to Namche Bazaar (3,440m )
✅Day 12: Trek from Namche Bazaar (3,440m) Lukla (2,850m )
✅Day 13: Fly back to Kathmandu (1400m ) from Lukla
✅Day 14 : Final Departure

📍Stoos, Switzerland 🇨🇭
Follow @hike_camp__ For More..

Getting to Stoos
1. Drive to the Schwyz-Schlattli funicular station:
• Address: Schlattli, 6433 Schwyz, Switzerland.
• Parking is available near the base station of the Stoos funicular.
• Ensure you arrive early, especially during weekends or peak seasons, as parking spots can fill up quickly.
2. Take the Stoosbahn Funicular:
• The Stoosbahn is the steepest funicular in the world and takes you from Schlattli up to the car-free village of Stoos in just a few minutes.
• Tickets: Purchase tickets for the funicular at the station or online to save time.

The Hike

Starting Point: Klingenstock
• From Stoos village, take the chairlift to Klingenstock.
• The chairlift ride offers stunning views and saves time and energy before starting the ridge hike.

The Ridge Hike: Klingenstock to Fronalpstock
• Duration: 3-4 hours (7 km).
• Highlights:
• Stunning panoramic views of the surrounding mountains (e.g., Mythen, Rigi, Pilatus).
• Views of Lake Lucerne and the countless peaks of central Switzerland.
• Well-marked paths and a mix of steep sections, ridges, and scenic spots.

End Point: Fronalpstock
• At Fronalpstock, take in the breathtaking 360-degree views.
• From here, take the chairlift back down to Stoos village.
